narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you did 154, you know what 155 is. Quizes are a bit harder, but Shen laoshi is great and generous with the reading. She's great!
The TA was very energetic and easy to talk to. She spoke at a level of Chinese that challenged me to improve my listening and conversational skills.
good course to take after CHNS 151-
Not a lot of work but can get a little dry at times

Initially I thought of Chinese 155 as just a great way to keep up my former levels of Chinese, but I ended up learning so much more than I thought I would! I also have heard from students in the literature classes that I was considering that Chinese 155 is much more effective at teaching vocabulary or helping with grammar, which seems to be true. I definitely learned a lot of grammar!
